.<br><br>Some will tell you to focus on wisdom. Paladins get lots of HPs and can heal, so mana is more important. How much mana you have will determine how long you solo before you stop and meditate. Likewise, no one in your group should die so long as you've got mana left.<br><br>Some will tell you stamina. Stamina equals HPs, thus your more likely to survive a close fight. Stamina is much harder to raise than Wisdom with gear. The other benefit is with 100+ stamina you no longer suffer the bad effects of being fatigued.<br><br>I personally would do 10 wisdom 10 stamina if I was human. If that's not for you, I would add 20 to stamina just to get the benefits of 100 stamina.<br><br>Qeynos is much better than Freeport for starting out. The best way to level is in dungeons and Blackburrow (near Qeynos) rules over the Befallen (near Freeport). Likewise, the Qeynos hills, Everfrost, and Wests Karana are much better designed than the Commonlands, North Ro, and Oasis.<br> <p><html><head><title></title></head><body><img src=http://home.insight.rr.com/cylria/cylriafvrelax.jpg><BR>Cylria Silversong<BR>Minstrel of the Twins<BR>Firiona Vie<BR></body></html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujaelprayerblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jael Prayerblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 98<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/16/02 12:18:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=55.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What stats to increase?</span><hr size=1> If you start with a Human, go Sta and Wis, the Str is sufficient, as there is a lot of str stuff out there for cheap.  Sta = Hp which is what all tanks need, so any sta is better than no sta.  Wis helps extremely in the highend game with HWoP.  Any points allocated to those stats wont be wasted.   <p><center><img src="http://www.illumincathari.com/images/profile/jael_sig.jpg"><center>Level 59 Paladin of Solusek Ro<center><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=145351>My Profile</a><center></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm20.showPrevMessage?topicID=55.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm20.showNextMessage?topicID=55.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=55.topic&index=2><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm20.emailToFriend?topicID=55.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm20.threadControl?topicID=55.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm20.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=55.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm20.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=55.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><o